OL,3,CDad forced to carry disabled son up
OL,4,Cstairs to flat will get new home
OL,6,F"We anticipate that Mr Murray and his
OL,7,Ffamily will be able to move into their
OL,8,Fnew home this week and we will
OL,9,Fcontinue to support them in any way we
OL,10,Fcan."
OL,12,FFor seven months, Mr Murray had been
OL,13,Fsearching every night on the Housing
OL,14,FAssociation's property pool.
OL,16,FSpeaking last week, Stephen said he'd
OL,17,Ffelt like was getting no support,
OL,18,Fadding: "I had to take my children
OL,19,Faway from the situation they were in
OL,20,Fto give them a better life, but I feel
OL,21,Flike they've gone backwards.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
