OL,3,CDad forced to carry disabled son up
OL,4,Cstairs to flat will get new home
OL,6,F"They're frozen in time because
OL,7,Fthere's so much they should be getting
OL,8,Fbut they're not. There's no light at
OL,9,Fthe end of the tunnel, it's just
OL,10,Fgetting dimmer and dimmer."
OL,12,FStephen was concerned his son's health
OL,13,Fwas being affected by the limited
OL,14,Fspace and not being able to use his
OL,15,Fson's specialist wheelchair, leg
OL,16,Fbraces and upright stand in the flat.
OL,18,FMost people with cerebral palsy have
OL,19,Fmobility issues, but regular exercise
OL,20,Fand play are crucial for maintaining
OL,21,Fand improving their physical strength.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
