OL,3,CDad forced to carry disabled son up
OL,4,Cstairs to flat will get new home
OL,6,FAfter receiving the news that they had
OL,7,Fsecured a house, local MP Derek Twigg
OL,8,Fsaid: "I am delighted that following
OL,9,Fthe intervention of myself, my team
OL,10,Fand ITV's Granada Reports that Stephen
OL,11,Fand his children were last week moved
OL,12,Fto a hotel and into accessible rooms,
OL,13,Fwhich means that Stephen is no longer
OL,14,Fhaving to carry his son with Cerebral
OL,15,FPalsy up and down stairs."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/9
